[Student "S"]
{With four fast winners SOUTH should think about game. The best approach is usually to 
use 2NT to find out more about NORTH's hand.

SOUTH found out that NORTH has good opening strength, and, most importantly, either the 
\HA or \HK. Now that she doesn't 
have to worry about the opponents taking the first five \H tricks 
she bids 3NT.}

